track_notes: Parking by side of farm track on Glen Afton NS631080. From the farm gate at Blackcraig you soon reach a roughly graded track which turns to earth just before Quintin Knowe, where you turn right and follow the fence until you see the cairn and cut across. We climbed the stile near the carin and continued to the trig where we found some shelter just below it from the wind and rain. It took us 95 mins to reach the trig point which was open for the pole.
track_title: A steady and mostly gradual ascent

track_notes: From the parking at Blackcraig follow the track to Blackcraig Hill. Continue on over Blacklorg Hill to the line of Pylons. You can decide here if you want to do the circuit over Alwat and Alhang. I elected to follow the road down and then up the Afton Water valley to the last sheep fold then via Millanoch Hill to Windy Standard. The return is mainly on the windfarm roads. Walk time about 6h with a day of 11hr for activations and other stops.
track_title: Blackcraig Hill and Windy Standard in one walk
